    <label>George Floyd Royal Flush</label>
    <description>While it is unknown who George Floyd is, the comedic packaging seems to indicate that "a George Floyd" is a derogatory slang term for an Urb-World criminal. What is known, though, is its effects. This sticky numbing psychite paste is laced with a cocktail of stimulant additives, principally Bentanyl-brand fentanyl and asbestos. While it is cheap to produce and extremely pleasurable to use, it is exceptionally addictive. The George Floyd Royal Flush is known for destroying the lives of people in inner cities in the overpopulated Urb-Worlds. \n \n It is so potent that it takes the user's breath away...</description>
